content: Only played first few missions of the campaign, and, the tutorial, but for the price it's very attractive!

Addictive and challenging, even when having completed the game. Once all missions are finished you can work on earning more achievements and on the expansion. If you choose to restart you can make it through the early stages quickly. The goals are the same but missions are different each time.

Not content being a fantastic bug free digital adaptation of the boardgame, this adds a marvelous single player campaign in addition to multiplayer.
Good campaign mode, definitely a learning curve to this game but experience improves substantially once you get the hang of it. No complaints.
This is my favorite board game and the mobile game does it justice! Thank you so much to all the devs who worked on the game and the mobile adaptation

Jeez, just realized that I've had this game (including the expansion) for about 6 years and still haven't rated it. Long overdue. Amazing game. I am super happy that I found it. I can sit here all day praising the gameplay, real-time vs turn-based, the humourous campaign, the challenges, etc. But what I really like is pass-and-play. It makes it easy to play a relaxing game with friends without them buying it. Amazing game. Please fix catapult interaction with hybrid cargo/batteries. Love you

I can't overstate how bad the writing is
Great game, no bugs, five stars.

Cool and easy to play.

Stellar game. My favourite boardgame turned into a fantastic mobile game. The aesthetic has transferred wonderfully. Music matches brilliantly. It's not just a lazy port, the devs put real time and love into making this a fully fleshed out game in its own right. Complete with a great single player campaign and online which can be done in live real time or pass and play. 5/5.

The campaign is awesome. The difficulty of the AI progresses throughout the campaign, and the AI ships are a fun and challenging opponents. More importantly the GUI is well designed and easy to use on a small-screen'd phone.
great make of genial board game. classy funny story and good character lines.

As a fussy mobile gamer, I must say that this is a truly fantastic mobile version of a classic board game. The design & implementation is superb. On top of that, the single player campaign is interesting and very humorous, and the pass-and-play mode works well for a family on the road who cannot take the original game with them. The addition of the turn-based build mode is a nice touch, especially for those who find the real-time mode too stressful. Highly recommended. A worthwhile purchase!

Generally a very good, faithful recreation of the original. A few annoying bugs, however. Notably that my profile keeps getting reset to red so I have to go back and change it back to green regularly :( Overall though, very much worth the money. Some interesting new mechanics and a great adaptation of the board game. PS. The expansion is great, though difficult :D

The single player game is great, except when you get to the very end, where the AI is far too good for me to beat in real-time ship building. Maybe it's my 7" screen and my old reflexes, but I do better with the board game against my friends.   But up the final race I enjoyed the game immensely!  Multiplayer is a mixed bag. I've had to abandon about a third of my online games due to various bugs, which sucks and makes me not want to play it any more. And yes, I've avoided mixing platforms and kept it updated.  The SP campaign was definitely worth the sale price I paid, but I'm not sure I'd pay full price for it just yet due to the poor online implementation. *UPDATE August 2015* Multiplayer stability seems to have improved. Unfortunately it's hard to know by how much. I still end up with players replaced by bots regularly and who knows if they just stopped playing or were unable to play due to the same old bugs?

There are lots of really fun board games out there, but most don't translate well into a digital form. For most, the problem is there is just too much "bits" floating around for a small screen app to adapt well enough.  Galaxy Trucker is a board game with dozens (maybe even hundreds) of tiles, and with a lot going on. I had my reservations going into this one, to be honest. How glad I was to be proven wrong!  The game does all the things that make the original board game great, and then adds an amazing campaign mode, some new ship designs, and all the humor the original was known for, only applied in more things.  This is a must for anyone. It's not just a great board game adaptation: it's a great video game on its own right.

Will 5-star when it works on landscape devices. Forced portrait orientation makes it unusable on landscape devices (TVs and gamepad-integrated devices) because the pointer no longer matches the logical screen orientation. As a board game, it "should" run on the household's central entertainment box (tv).
replyContent: You are right. We are sorry, this game is not designed for such devices (TVs). We are working on it right now, but current version shouldn't be enabled for them.

At least partially because the evaluation phase is full of flavor animations, which in my opinion take too long.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback. Yes, we are preparing the expansions. The speed of anims has been set after the hours of user testing, slow enough to be clear for newbies and fast for the experienced wolfs. Please notice the fast forward button in flight. The turn based is slow intentionally. We are considering an user option to set the anim speed.

I love playing this board game with friends, so the only thing missing from this is everyone screaming at each other. Also, I hope that some of the expansions get added in at some point, as it gets even crazier!
Great board game crossover
Runs beautifully on Note 2. Great conversion from the boardgame. Love the multiplayer options.

Been waiting to play this game since Pocket Tactics raved on about it on the Ipad release date. I'm not dissapointed after my wait either, in fact it's alot better than I expected a whole heap of fun to play. :-)
A whimsical space romp that is easy to pick up and hard to put down.
Really making great use of the medium: animations of meteors flying past your ship, an interesting campaign unlocking effects, loads of fun. And just £2 during the launch promotion! Get it now!
Translates to mobile devices very well. Smooth play, fun single player, all around good stuff.
Lots of funny remarks, I like Czech humour! Especially in the campaign
Fantasitc implementation of the boardgame.
I have the board game but the campaign mode here is worth the price alone. Great game!
True to the game mechanics. Fun to play
Great adaptation of the awesome board game
Great port of the boardgame
Loved the card version and have been waiting eagerly for this one. Am not disappointed.
Love it

Never rated anything before but I thought this one was a must! Never played the board game version but after the digital version will endeavor to pick it up! My one improvement request would be to receive notifications when it is my turn in a turn by turn multiplayer game!
Humorous and plays wonderfully. Campaign mode is incredibly engaging.
I was doubtful that the frantic tile-grabbing gameplay would translate well, but it does. I'm enjoying the campaign mode, neat challenges so far.
Gives an accurate feel of the chaos, mayhem, and incredible amount of fun offered by the board game. Can't say enough good about it!
this adaptation is a great way to play when you can't get a group together for a game. The campaign mode is a super cool addition. Bring on Space Alert mobile next!
This is a really well done electronic adaptation of one of my favorite games. It makes me happy to see the quality and, just as important, the spirit and goofiness that is evident.
An amazing port of a brilliant game. Buy it!
Convinced me to buy the board game.
Great game! Very smooth gameplay! Tons of fun.
Could have more simultaneous local saves.
Been waiting for this one to come to Android and am not disappointed.
Interesting and fun rendition of the boardgame.
Fantastic representation of the table top version.
Just like the board game, and the campaign mode is fabulous!
Been looking for a new board game, decided to try before i bought it. Super fun and great priced at $3
Haven't played there board game and think I'll have to now.
The fun chaos of the cardboard version is here in spades - with less fiddley bits and set-up!
Great quick board game
If you like Galaxy truckers or board gaming in general, you must buy this game.
Great game, nice implementation

This is a really well put together recreation of the board game. It goes way beyond just a playable version of it, with well done graphics and effects. Even if you've never played before, it's tons of fun. Would definitely recommend it.
AWESOME!
Game is great! Made purchasing the board game even easier!
Love this portable version of one of my top played boardgames. The campaign mode is excellent.
Worth the buy.

I'm an avid board gamer, and never having played the physical version of this,  I didn't know what I was missing!  It just shot to the top of my list. Can't wait to get this on the table,  but the app is really good in the meantime.  Love the campaign mode!
Really nice game. Been interested in playing for a while and have been really enjoying the campaign so far.
F$!#ing awesome. Perfect depiction of the board game.
The campaign even makes sense out of it all. Love it.
Excellent implementation of the cardboard version. Loses the schadenfreude when playing solo though.
Well thought out port of board game to mobile. The single player campaign is a great edition. Plays surprisingly well on a phone when I first assumed it was tablet-only
Shows how mobile development should be done. Works great on tablet and phone. Best mobile board game adaptation?

The iPad One issue where you can't type in a long email created an account with MY username and I can't recover my password/username... very frustrating then I got logged into it and no matter what password I try it won't fix it when I log in game.  Also it acts like you can type in a new email address once logged in but if you try to change it says "wrong email". More frustrating above all is how there is no support/contact email address on the form so you have no idea how to reach the devs.

The game itself is great but is anyone else having an issue where you can't input text for profile names?  I was given a default name of Trucker so I can play, but I can't set up additional profiles for hot seat.  Haven't tried to set up online yet, hope that works when my friends grab this...         Edit: after downloading a new keyboard from Google it works fine.  Was using my tablet's default, an Asus keyboard.
replyContent: Hi. Try to use a default/other android keyboard. Sometimes killing the app and starting it again helps too. You can delete the default profile and create new one. Sorry for the inconvenience, we'll try to fix these little incompatibilities.

content: A fantastic app version of the Vlada Chivatil classic board game of frantic action puzzle solving. If you love the board game, you will love this re-creation.
Top notch stuff!
Excellent implementation! Download NOW!
Good version of the Boardgame
It's just like playing the original board game, i.e. chaotic, bonkers fun. Love it!
Anyone who is a fan of the game will love this. Perfect port.
The only minor problem is the excessive need to slide everything is hurting my finger a bit.
They've managed to take the chaotic fun if Galaxy Trucker and faithfully port it to digital.
Fun board game!
This is soo awesome definitely one of the best games I've played for a while love the board game and love this app just as much
Seems to be a petty good adaptation of the board game
I didn't think you'd be able to translate this game onto a phone, but they've done a fantastic job.
Hoping it becomes a bit more configurable down the road.  It would be great to be able to skip the animations.
Best Boardgame adaptation on Android
Easily one of the best implementations of a board game to digital.
Pleasantly surprised by the addition of the single player campaign. Great game
... on my tablet. Works surprisingly well on my phone too. This is a good un.
Ladies and gentlemen, they hit it out of the park on this one. I LOVE this digital version and see myself spending a good chunk of time building super cool ships. Love it!
Great board game, and a wonderful implementation.
Great implementation of one of my  favorite board games.
Fantastic adaptation of a fantastic board game. Watch with delight as your speed-built sewer ship is torn to pieces by meteors. 11/10 would be eaten by aliens again.

Really captures the spirit of the board game with CGE's trademark humour. Fantastic and unique gameplay, effortless controls, great performance on TF300T, and what looks to be a vast amount of content for the incredibly reasonable price. I just know I'll be getting lost in this game, and eagerly looking forward to the next CGE game.
Great job! Love how fluid and smoothly it plays.
Solid port with rock solid tutorial. Gameplay is nearly identical to the board game, and just as fun as the original. App quality is top notch as well.
A very enjoyable digital version of an awesome board game.
This is a lot of fun!
Working well on Note 4

Until more friends pick this up, solo campaign it is. Lucky for me it is sweet. Lots of different types of missions to force you to build unique ships whereas multiplayer usually benefits from a well rounded ship. Just got done being an escort which required loading up on guns and engines while my partner had all cargo. :-)
App hits on all cylinders, keep on trucking with this app, all night long! Okay bad attempts at humor aside this is a very well done app that lives up to the board game tremendously well.
Chvatil-worthy
One of my favorite board games, now on my phone :D
Runs very well on the Nexus 5! This is a great adaptation of the board game. The animations and music are top notch.
